HEADWORD: Juger
<hw>Ju"ger</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>jugerum</ets>.]</ety> <def>A Roman measure of land, measuring
28,800 square feet, or 240 feet in length by 120 in breadth.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

